Two crucial parameters to quantify the structure and stability of perovskites are the tolerance factor (t) and the octahedral factor (μ) [35, 36]. The tolerance factor is the ratio of the bond lengths of A–X and B–X in an idealized solid-sphere model. Mathematically, it can be expressed as:t=RA+RX√2RB+RX\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
